cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles west of Camagüey, Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Moving northeast across central Cuba this morning, then expected to turn north-northwest and pass near or over the Florida Keys tonight before drifting westward over the southeastern Gulf of Mexico.

weather_observation.watch_coast: Hurricane Watch from Deerfield Beach to Bonita Beach, including the Florida Keys; Storm Surge Watch Golden Beach to Bonita Beach and the Keys
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning Brevard/Volusia County line southward around Florida peninsula to Englewood, including the Florida Keys and Florida Bay
weather_observation.impacted_coast: South-central Cuba, northwestern Bahamas, South Florida including the Keys, and eventually the eastern Gulf Coast
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible mid-week with a small (≤6%) chance of reaching tropical-storm force gusts.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Guidance indicates 2–3 ft of surge possible from Flagler/Volusia County Line to Altamaha Sound; Jacksonville could see minor coastal flooding but values above 3 ft are not expected.
weather_observation.rainfall: Outer rain-bands may bring 1–3 inches of rain Wednesday–Thursday.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Elevated surf and dangerous rip currents along NE Florida beaches.
